Six members of the same family died Saturday in an accident involving a saloon car and a lorry in Ruai along Eastern Bypass in&nbsp;Nairobi. The group was travelling in a Noah vehicle when it collided with the lorry. Police say the driver of the saloon car survived and was rushed to hospital in a serious condition. The six were from a graduation event in Kakamega headed for Kangundo when the accident happened at about 5am. Police are investigating the incident. ALSO READ: Family Bank rues Sh2 billion bond